title: Texas GLO, Audubon Animal Sancuarties, Texas, 1997
name: Texas GLO, Audubon Animal Sancuarties, Texas, 1997
description:
Sanctuaries managed by the National Audubon Society or local Audubon Society chapters in Texas coastal bays. Digitized by Texas General Land Office from lease documents.
Most of these areas are state-owned tracts leased from the Texas General Land Office. Also includes representation of the Sabal Palm Sanctuary owned by the National Audubon Society.

properties.NAME: Rattlesnake Island, Ayres Island, and Roddy Island
